cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the Quality of Experience (QoE) for video streaming applications in a network with Long-Range-Dependent (LRD) input traffic. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the QoE of multimedia streaming, specifically video streaming. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses partial differential equations (PDEs) and Laplace Transform to solve the analytical model, which falls under the domain of information theory. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the tradeoff among different metrics incorporating user preferences on buffering ratio, startup delay, and perceived quality, which falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the performance of video streaming applications in a network with LRD input traffic and proposes an analytical framework to investigate QoE.
